
	1) Create virtual env: 
	c:\>python -m venv c:\path\to\myenv
	
	After this, you can see this folder is created.  c:\path\to\myenv\.venv
	
	From <https://docs.python.org/3/library/venv.html> 
	
	2) Check pip version, 
	py -m pip --version
	
From <https://packaging.python.org/en/latest/tutorials/installing-packages/#creating-and-using-virtual-environments> 
